description.plain:
Michael Ian Olmo (b. March 25, 1999), better known by his stage name iann dior, is a recording artist from Arecibo, Puerto Rico. He moved to Corpus Christi, Texas at a young age, where he grew up for most of his early life.

He began releasing music in 2017 under the mononym Olmo, and stage name Lil Rock, though his come-up is a blur due to having it seemingly covered following his signing.

With his first release under Internet Money for “cutthroat,” iann worked with producer Nick Mira who has produced for artists such as Juice WRLD, XXXTENTACION and Lil Skies. He has worked with artists such as Bernard Jabs and PnB Rock on his tracks “molly” and “romance361” respectively.

iann quickly gained attention in early 2019, with him signing to TenThousand Projects in the following April.

On November 8, 2019, iann dropped his debut studio album, Industry Plant. The project included featured artists such as Trippie Redd, Gunna and Travis Barker on the tracks “gone girl,” “Strings” and “Darkside” respectively.

The artist planned releasing his first studio EP, I’m Gone on June 5, 2020. However, due to tumultuous conditions particularly in the United States around the time with the #BlackLivesMatter movement, iann dior postponed the release of the EP to June 12, 2020. This project contained features with artists such as Travis Barker and Machine Gun Kelly.

iann dior and his friend 24kGoldn released a collaboration single named “Mood” on July 24, 2020. Both have previously worked together on albums such as Industry Plant and nothings ever good enough. During the week ending October 24, 2020, “Mood” peaked at #1 on the Hot 100. It is both 24kGoldn and iann dior’s first song to top the chart.

songs.title: ​gone girl

description.plain:
“gone girl“ sees iann dior connecting with Trippie Redd for a track about their relationship struggles.

The track was first officially teased on Iann’s Instagram on June 30, 2019, but the post has since been taken down.

songs.title: ​emotions

description.plain: “emotions” is the first single from iann dior’s debut album nothings ever good enough. It is an upbeat emo-rap song in which dior discusses a broken relationship and it’s outcome. The track was produced by Nick Mira, who has worked with XXXTENTACION, Juice WRLD, and Lil Skies for several other hits.

songs.title: ​molly

description.plain: ‘molly’ is the 4th track off of iann dior’s first album “nothings ever good enough”. It is talking about how a girl he knows is addicted to molly and is high and it is put over a really cool beat. iann dior and Bernard Jabs have great chemistry on this track and its an overall very very good song. you should totally go check this song out on spotify and the awesome music video on his YouTube channel.
